###

@NODE INTRO "Introduction"

   @{b}Introduction:@{ub}


  The  history of F-Bench starts there are now close to 3 years with one
  idea not very original: to achieve my own files manager.  Therefore  a
  meadow-version  alpha-béta lives the day... :-) A version very simple,
  few options available and, unfortunately with lot of bugs. And,  after
  3  minutes  of  use  my  A1200  rebooted  alone... Arff. Some weeks of
  programming later, a new version  appeared,  still  for  my  personnal
  use... Revised interfacing, possibility to create the button-menus and
  to copy, to erase and to rename files !!! :-). In short,  a  big  step
  forward.

  The  project  has  been  put of quoted during a good moment because of
  F-base  which  took  me  all  my  free  time.  In  January  1997,  the
  development  of  F-bench has started again. Lot of the original source
  code is modified and the interfacing is put back to the taste  of  the
  day.

  Two  versions are distributed on Aminet, without big success. The last
  public version is the V1.10 (October 3, 1997).

  But what that did he/it pass of October 3, 1997 to June 26, 1998?  All
  first,  a new project is born : ' TheBoss'. More or less 5 months were
  necessary to achieve it (it is a software  a  bit  like  ToolManager).
  F-Bench underwent as for him of the small daily retouchings, to remove
  the small imperfections and to add some new functions...

      Here is a summary of the main features of F-bench:

          - Internal detection of 35 types like:

                  * IFF/ILBM
                  * IFF Animation (Format ANIM5)
                  * GIF picture
                  * JPEG picture
                  * BMP picture
                  * PCX picture
                  * FLI/FLC animation
                  * Executable
                  * Text (ASCII)
                  * AmigaGuide 
                  * LHA packed files
                  * DMS packed disks
                  * LZX packed files
                  * IFF/8SVX Sample
                  * WAVE Sample
                  * Protracker module
                  * Octamed module
                  * Workbench's Icons
                  * Powerpacked file
                  * And more...

          - Preferences permitting have F-Bench to be setup very
            easily (Font, Screen, Palette...)

          - System compliant, fully multitasking

          - Colorful interfacing

          - Asynchrone multitasking (An opened window doesn't block
            the software...)

          - Easy to use

          - Allow to manage its programs and to create some 'macros buttons'

          - Possibility to rename, erase, copy, comment and protect the
            files. Possibility to execute a command line and to create
            a drawer.


                     @{b}F-Bench is a Shareware product @{ub}


@ENDNODE

