###

@NODE SYSTEM "Requiered System"

    @{b}Requiered System:@{ub}


  * You must have an Amiga :-)

  'diskfont.library' and 'locale.library' are needed.

  The file 'FCopy' is as indispensable.

  Finally, you must have the F-Bench.DATA file to benefit the detections
  of the different types of files.

  All it is provided :) !


@ENDNODE

###

@NODE INSTALL "Installation d'F-Bench"

    @{b}Installation:@{ub}


  To install F-Bench is a comfortable thing (in fact you can directly
  to use it. Particular installation is not necessary).


    @{b}Automatic Solution:@{ub}

  Click on the Install icon.


    @{b}Manual Solution:@{ub}

    * Create a new drawer.
    * Copy in theses files:

            - F-Bench               (main File)
            - F-Bench_Prefs         (File Preferences)
            - F-Bench_English.guide (File Doc)
            - FCopy                 (File System)
            - Catalogs/English      (File of localization)
            - F-Bench.DATA          (File Of Recognition)

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE USAGE "User Manual"

                       @{b}How to use F-Bench@{ub}


  F-Bench benefits an interfacing of the type 'all to screen'. In clear,
  there  is  not  any  menus.  It presents an advantage: you can use the
  right button of the mouse to push on the buttons. It  is  why  it  can
  have upto 2 differents actions per buttons.


      @{b}Main buttons:@{ub}

      DEVICES buttons (DF0:, RAM:, DH0:,...)

      Click on a these buttons to list the content of the volume in
    the activated window.

      @{"Configurable buttons" LINK CONFIGMENU} How to config the blank buttons?


      @{b}F-Bench internal commands:@{ub}

          they are located in the 'Commands' button submenu. It contains
          all the F-Bench commands and it can't be modified.

          Commands are:

 @{" Parent " LINK PARENT}                   @{"   Menu   " LINK MENU}                    @{" Parent " LINK PARENT}

                             @{" Exec.Com " LINK EXECUTE}
                             @{"  Delete  " LINK DELETE}
                             @{"   Copy   " LINK COPY}
                             @{"  Rename  " LINK RENAME}
                             @{"   All    " LINK ALL}
                             @{"   None   " LINK NONE}
                             @{" NewDrawer" LINK NEWDRAWER}
                             @{"  Comment " LINK COMMENT}
                             @{"  Protect " LINK PROTECT}
                             @{" Duplicate" LINK DUPLICATE}
                             @{"   Move   " LINK MOVE}
                             @{"  Select  " LINK SELECT}

                           @{"<" LINK ARROWS}@{"   Stop   " LINK STOP}@{">" LINK ARROWS}


    @{" ? " LINK AUTHOR}:  Makes  appear  one  window  containing  the information
  on the author and permits  to  know  if  the  version  of  F-Bench  is
  registered or not.

    @{b}'Rescan'@{ub}: Permits to rescan whole system to detect new mounted
    devices or new files in selected directories.


    @{b}General Usage:@{ub}

  To visualize the content of a drawer, double-click on that  index.  If
  you  make a simple-click, you select the index. (The color of the name
  becomes reversed).

  Double-click on the name of a file to get an information on this file.
  You  will  know thus if the file is recognized by F-Bench and you will
  be able to execute one or several command then relative to  this  type
  of file. A simple-click on a file select it or unselect it if the file
  was already selected.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE MENU "The 'Menu' button"

    @{b}The 'Menu' button:@{ub}

  This button allow to come back to the main menu. F-Bench proposes  one
  system  of  complete  program  management  and  permits the edition of
  'macro buttons' under the shape of menus. To have more information  on
  the profiles of menus, click @{" here " LINK CONFIGMENU}.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE PARENT "The 'Parent' buttons"

    @{b}The 'Parent' buttons:@{ub}


  They are located to the over of every window. They permit to come back
  in the previous index.

  Example:

  You are in the index 'DF0:F-Bench/'. Push on PARENT for to  come  back
  under the index 'DF0:'.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE EXECUTE "Execute a command line"

    @{b}Execute a command line:@{ub}


  This function simply permits  to  execute  a  line  of  command  under
  F-Bench. A window opens when you push on this button asking for you to
  bring in your command.

  Push on to Execute to launch your command or on to Cancel to close the
  window without executing the commmande.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE DELETE "Delete files"

   @{b}Delete files:@{ub}


  This Button permits you to  erase  all  files  and  drawers  that  you
  selected  previously.  A  window  will  open  for  you  to  ask  for a
  confirmation. Push on 'Yes' to launch the erasing of files or on  'No'
  to stop the operation.

  You  can  has  all moment to stop the suppression of files in pressing
  the button 'STOP'.

  However, all deleted files will remain deleted. Use this command  with
  precaution.

  Know  all  the  same  that it exists software permitting to recover to
  100% of files erased  by  accident  (ie:  DiskSALV,  a  shareware)  to
  condition  that  you  didn't recopy anything on your disk between time
  (what would provoke the ancient file bruising).

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE COPY "Copy files"

    @{b}Copy files:@{ub}


  This control permits to copy files  selected  of  the  present  window
  TOWARD the other window. It is necessary to select 2 drawers different
  to do the copy. If a file that you copy exist already  in  the  drawer
  destination,  a window will open for to ask for you if it is necessary
  to either replace it no.

  This control uses the control 'FCopy' system. It is the only  function
  that uses an external control for its own working.

  You  can  stop the copy of files at any time while pressing the button
  @{" Stop " LINK STOP}.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE RENAME "Rename files"

    @{b}Rename files:@{ub}


  This control permits you to rename all files that are selected of  the
  activated  window.  A  window will open for you to ask to bring in the
  new name for every file.

  If you selected several files and  that  you  don't  want  anymore  to
  continue  to rename these files, you can push on the button @{" Stop " LINK STOP}
  or click on the button of closing of the window.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE ALL "Select all"

    @{b}Select all files:@{ub}


  This control selects all files of the window merely in progress.


@ENDNODE

###

@NODE NONE "Unselect all files"

    @{b}Unselect all files:@{ub}


  This control unselect all selected files of the in progress window.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE NEWDRAWER "New Drawer"

    @{b}Make a new directory:@{ub}


  This  control  permits  to  create  a  new  directory  in  the  window
  activated.  A  window will open to ask for you to bring in the name of
  your new drawer.

  You can also choose to create  an  icon  or  no  for  this  drawer  in
  clicking  the  option  'Create  Icon'.  For  it,  you must have a file
  'def_drawer' in your index ' ENV:Sys '. Normally, this file exist.  If
  this file is not untraceable, no icon is created.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE COMMENT "Comment files"

    @{b}Comment files:@{ub}


  This commmande allow to associate a commentary to a file.  One  window
  will  open  to  permit  you  to  bring  in  your  new commentary. If a
  commentary already exists for this file, it will be displayed  in  the
  zone of foreclosure.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE PROTECT "Protect files"

    @{b}Protect files:@{ub}


  This control allow you to modify the different properties
  of files:

      - Hidden : ???

      - Script : Permits to give back executable a Script (File
                 containing some AmigaDOSs commands). This file won't have
                 more need of the control ' execute' to can
                 to be launched.

      - Pure   : Permits to determine a file so is ' pur' or no.
                 If a file is pure, it can be to execute in so much
                 that 'resident'.

      - Archive: Permits to know a file so is archived
                 (Flag used by certain Backup of Disk-hard)

      - Read   : Knowledge if the file can either be read no

      - Write  : To know if one can modify this file

      - Execute: To know if one can execute this file

      - Delete : To know if one can delete this file

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE DUPLICATE "Duplicate files"

    @{b}Duplicate files:@{ub}


  This control allow you to duplicate the chosen files. For  every  file
  will open a window where you should specify the name of the cloned new
  file.

  You can stop the operation has all moment while pushing on the  button
  @{" Stop " LINK STOP}.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE MOVE "Move files"

    @{b}Move files:@{ub}


  This control permits to move  the  chosen  files  toward  your  drawer
  destination,  that is to say that files are tower to tower copied then
  toward this drawer unobtrusive of the drawer source.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE SELECT "Select files"

    @{b}Select files:@{ub}


  This control permits to choose files thanks to the the use of  jockers
  standard AmigaOS (#?, ?...). All combinations are possible.

  Example:

  To select all files that end by '.info ' enter the following mask:

  @{b}#?.info@{ub}

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE STOP "Stop the current operation"

    @{b}Stop the current operation:@{ub}


  This button permits to stop an in progress operation.

  For example: copy, delete, rename, protect,...

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE ARROWS "copiers of drawers... :)"

  These 2 arrows permit to copy the content of the merely window of left
  toward the window of right or inversely.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE CONFIGMENU "Menus configuration"

   @{b}Configuration of menus:@{ub}


  To personalize a button, click with the right button of the  mouse  on
  the button to edit.

  A window will open permitting you to configure the button very easily.
  The button will be able to be very well a normal  button,  either  one
  button-drawer,  that  is  to  say  a  button  that  will contain other
  buttons.

  Bring in the name of your button as well as the line of commands to to
  do at the time of the support on this button.

  You  can  put  in  your line of command the reserved word '%sf' to all
  place of the line (but only one time in the line).

  @{b}%sf@{ub} = selected files

  Therefore, at the time of the execution of the control,  %sf  will  be
  replaced by the names of all files selected.

  Other  reserved  words will be able to appear in the future version to
  permit a better management of buttons.

  Example of command line: C:VT %sf

  The support of this button is going to launch the VT program (ViewTek)
  and  will  enter  in  parameter  the  selected  files  (convenient  to
  visualize the pictures).

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE FBPREFS "How to use FBench_Prefs"

   @{b}How to use FBench_Prefs@{ub}

  This utility allows you to configure F-Bench to your perference.

  It is very simple to use. Very  self-explanatory.  You  have  probably
  seen similiar preference or configuration utilities many times before.
  They are a usual part of many programs.

    @{b}WARNING:@{ub} The ASL.Library is required but is NOT  included  in
  original archive. If you DO NOT have the ASL.library, you will find it
  freely available on the AmiNET.

  The F-BPrefs must be in the same directory as F-Bench. Do NOT  put  it
  your SYSTEM Preferences drawer. It DOES NOT Belong there.

   @{b}Basic Usage:

      @{b}Screen Font@{ub}:  Choose the Font used by the F-Bench screen.
                    The size of this Font must be 8 or greater.
                    Smaller point-size fonts are not supported.

                    Default Font: Topaz/8.

      @{b}Edition Font@{ub}: Same as Screen Font.

      @{b}Screen Mode@{ub}:  Select the Screen Mode used by F-Bench. The
                    size must be 640 x 200 or greater.
    
                    Default Screen: PAL 640 x 256 -  8 Colors.


      @{b}File Configuration@{ub}:

  Allow to setup the window of Recognition of files. For that  to  make,
  select,  thanks  to  the buttons the type of file that you interresse.
  Then, bring in the title of the window  for  this  type  of  file  and
  choose  the number of necessary Gadgets to Treat your file. Enter then
  the line of command wanted.

  Example: You want to be able to display a IFF picture  under  F-Bench.
  Select  '  IFF/ILBM Picture' Mettez Picture IFF in the Button ' Window
  Title' Fixez the number of Buttons has 1. (Number gadgets)

  Enter in ' Name' Voir Enters in ' Command' Path and name of the Viewer
  Enter in ' Command (End) ' NIL:

  Make in the same way for the other formats of files.

@ENDNODE

###

@NODE SHARE "The shareware concept"

    @{b}The shareware concept:@{ub}


  F-Bench is Shareware, what means that  if  you  want  to  receive  the
  complete version of F-Bench you must send a (weak) contribution to the
  @{" author " LINK AUTHOR}.

  It will permit you to record you  close  to  the @{" author "  LINK AUTHOR}
  and to receive a personal keyfile, that will permit you to use
  fully F-Bench and all next versions of F-Bench.

  You can receive your key of 2 different manners:

  * By e-mail
  * By the regular mail

  The amount of the contribution for F-Bench is fixed to 15 US$, 10 Ł or
  20 DM.

  The  version  of  demonstration is entirely functional but the program
  will close itself automatically after 5 minutes of use.


      @{b}Don't forget : the future of F-Bench depends on you...@{ub}

@ENDNODE

