@NODE HISTORI "F-bench history"

  F-Bench history:

        @{b} July 10, 1998: V2.00@{ub}

   * Improven graphic interfacing. New look (that is that that you in
     tells?).
   * Possibility to remove the gray lines and the word ' (Drawer) ' before
     drawer names
   * FBench_Prefs has been improven extensively
   * A few new types of files have been added
   * Addition of a profile file already operational in archives it
     (to show march how profiles of file types
   * Guide file fully rewritten (French and English)
   * Removed numerous bugs
   * Further optimizations
   * Addition of a demonstration picture to show F-Bench how can
     to be configured (Font, colors...)


        @{b}November 1997: V1.20@{ub} - not set down on Aminet

   * Routine of file sortings frankly fast: sorted out 426 files
     in 14 Ticks (14/50 of seconds) on an A1230/50 against several
     seconds for the old routine
   * Command 'Copy' optimized again (The speed of copy of files of one
     index has the other has been multiplied by 2)
   * Addition of sliders (In short!). That done make CooOOooLs more no?
   * Addition of the function to choose files that permit to select
     files with the help of a mask (ex: #? .info, #?jaco?,..)
   * The function 'Move' has been improven extensively: the displacement
     of files on the same unit (DF0:, DH0:) is now really fast =:-)
   * F-Bench_Prefs was completely recoded (As for F-base),
     it's smaller, more beautiful, faster... In short, better d$-)
   * Revised interfacing, more professional :-)
   * Re-optimized code (I won more than 10 kb on the executable size)
   * A lot of bugs fixes
   * More need of 'FRun'. The execution of files via F-Bench is now faster.
   * More need of 'FInfo'. The 'Rescan' function is therefore of fastest and
     the loading of departure is also a little accelerated.
   * The screen of F-Bench is now PUBLIC! It is very useful.
     Besides colors one been especially adjusted so that the
     window intuitions really have a look cool on the screen
     of F-Bench.
   * The serving buffer has manage files has been reduced from 70 kb
     of ram to ZERO, NOTHING, NULL. Since this version, F-bench use,
     a dynamic system of memory allocation for every files.
     F-Bench can manage an INFINITE number of files (Before,
     it was limited to 2000...). The memory is not wasted anymore.
   * Optimization of the file display. It is now very
     very fast (30% faster than before).
   * Complete localization of F-Bench (via the locale.library).
     Whoever can create are therefore own file language for
     to have F-Bench in its favorite language :-).


        @{b}October 3, 1997: V1.10@{ub}

   * NUMEROUS BUGS Fixed...
   * Possibility to create an icon when one creates a new drawer.
   * Possibility to modify the palette (AGA and no-AGA)
   * 'Copy' improved (Choice of the sense of the copy,...)
   * I added a button 'ReScan' that simply permits to detect
     if new volumes/deviceses went up (RAD: etc...). This boutton
     rescan as the content of indexes listed in windows.
   * 2 new functions have been added: 'Move', 'Duplicate'.
   * 11 new recognized file types (AVI, MOV... and XPK (SMPL and SQUASH)
     what permits to manage compressed Mods/Samples/Texts with an ease
     very disconcerting d:-D)
   * The type 'Text ASCII' is well good managed.
   * Mega-optimizations (For information, the size of the file has been reduced
     of 170 kb to 131 kb nothing that for the fun... and for the speed/reliability)
   * Some imperceptible things but indispensable: -)
     + of securities at the time of the opening of polices, of the screen, of
windows,
     AND, most important, my new interfacing has a IMPECCABLE behavior
     in the Amiga multitasking environment !

        @{b}March 4, 1997: V1.00@{ub}

   * First public version (Aminet)

@ENDNODE

